->String is a collection of characters

->in simple language we can say that string which is a one kined of array or we can say taht 
characters of array

syntax:

char name[size]={};
 or 
 char name[6]={'h','e','l','l','o','\0'}
                                     |
                                     v
                                     this is called null character
agar hum user se name mange ge to scanf("%s",&name); ye likhen ge to phir hum name to mga lenge par agr jese 
mene mohammed or fir space dunga to scanf bad vale name ko nhin likhe ga is ke liye hum gets ka use kar te hai 
is me bus gets (name); likh den ge to ye pura line le lega space ke sath bhi 

in bild functions #include<string.h>
for size -> strlen(array name)
for concatenation{marjing}->strcat(s1,s2);
          {agr humko secund me je se bas do hi caracter marj karna ho to strncat(s1,s2,2); ese likhenge}
for copy -> strcpy(s1,s2);
          {agr humko secund me je se bas do hi caracter copy karna ho to strncpy(s1,s2,2); ese likhenge}
for compare -> strcmp(s1,s2);
          {agr humko secund me je se bas do hi caracter compare karna ho to strncmp(s1,s2,2); ese likhenge}
for reverse -> strrev(s1);


whe we want to connvert any character into lowercase there in on method
to lower()

and to convert any carecter onto uppercase there is one method
to upper()

but bhoth method are connected with c type header file #include<ctype.h>

for convert to upper case -> toupper(s1);
for convert to lower case -> tolower(s1);
